34:17.040 --> 34:20.010
Hey.
Come on, you're his friend.

34:20.080 --> 34:22.560
You were there, right?
What happened?

34:22.679 --> 34:24.569
Come on, kid,
don't stonewall us.

34:24.679 --> 34:27.047
He ain't looking at ya.

34:27.120 --> 34:29.327
Come on, it's just us,
marine to marine.

34:29.400 --> 34:31.880
Jarhead to jarhead.

34:31.960 --> 34:34.167
It was fucked.

34:34.280 --> 34:36.168
Me and Sheppard
and three other guys

34:36.239 --> 34:37.844
were all day humping
school supplies

34:37.920 --> 34:40.924
We had tablets,
pencils, new books.

34:41.000 --> 34:43.400
It' was our last' run-

34:43.520 --> 34:46.251
Anyway, we was always stopping
at this little store

34:46.360 --> 34:48.043
we called Abdul's Haji Mart.

34:48.080 --> 34:49.922
We'd have Haji Cokes.

34:50.000 --> 34:51.728
It was my turn to make the run,

34:51.800 --> 34:53.802
but Sheppard said
he'd do it, so he goes

34:53.880 --> 34:57.043
and we're bullshitting
and this raghead comes up,

34:57.120 --> 34:58.724
shouts out...

35:00.040 --> 35:02.441
"Allah Akbar"...

35:02.560 --> 35:04.244
Whatever the fuck.

35:04.320 --> 35:06.448
"God is great."

35:06.560 --> 35:08.528
Puts a cap in Shep's head.

35:13.080 --> 35:14.969
Jesus.

35:15.080 --> 35:16.923
What happened next?

35:17.960 --> 35:20.247
Shit, man, we went off.

35:20.320 --> 35:22.721
Lit 'em all up.

35:22.800 --> 35:24.450
The raghead, Abdul,

35:24.600 --> 35:26.204
damn near whole fuckin' hood.

35:28.840 --> 35:31.446
Carried Larry back
to the Hummer and went home.

35:34.000 --> 35:35.445
You know, the kid's supposed

35:35.520 --> 35:37.443
to get the Bronze Star
behind this.

35:37.520 --> 35:39.090
Yeah.

35:39.160 --> 35:40.605
He'll get the star.

35:40.680 --> 35:42.444
The more stars
the better, right?

35:42.520 --> 35:44.568
Yeah.
- Right.

36:01.960 --> 36:03.121
Okay...

36:03.200 --> 36:05.282
We can '2' tell him about this.

36:05.360 --> 36:06.771
We can't?
- No.

36:06.840 --> 36:08.763
Let him have his Bronze Star.
- Shit.

36:08.840 --> 36:11.844
Let him have his burial at
Arlington with full honors.

36:11.920 --> 36:13.729
Let him have his hero.

36:13.800 --> 36:16.929
Lord knows the man ain't had nothing
but pain in his life lately.

36:17.000 --> 36:18.923
In other words,
let him have the lie.

36:19.000 --> 36:22.368
Think about it, Sal.
What's more important?

36:22.480 --> 36:23.845
I don't know.

36:23.960 --> 36:25.883
But it's never the lie.

36:34.320 --> 36:36.766
Sal...

36:36.880 --> 36:38.041
Sal.

36:40.560 --> 36:42.881
I'm sorry, sir, but there's
always a sound reason

36:43.000 --> 36:45.002
for my recommendations.

36:50.360 --> 36:52.601
Sal, he doesn't have
a face anymore.

37:11.080 --> 37:13.128
You got to be a man now.

37:15.360 --> 37:17.010
Hey, mister.

37:17.080 --> 37:18.525
Hey, Sal.

37:20.520 --> 37:22.921
How did this boy wind up dead?

37:23.000 --> 37:24.365
I beg your pardon?

37:24.440 --> 37:26.841
I think it's
a pretty simple question.

37:26.920 --> 37:28.206
What happened?

37:28.280 --> 37:30.601
The lance corporal
acquitted himself

37:30.720 --> 37:33.041
with dignity and honor,
and he died a hero.

37:33.120 --> 37:34.849
Yeah, but I mean, they're...

37:34.920 --> 37:36.445
they're all heroes, ain't they?

37:36.560 --> 37:39.211
That they are, sir.
Yeah. All heroes.

37:39.280 --> 37:41.362
No question.

37:41.440 --> 37:44.046
How did it happen that this boy

37:44.120 --> 37:47.124
was shot in the back
of the head like a fucking dog?

37:49.440 --> 37:51.090
He was a brave marine,

37:51.160 --> 37:53.242
credit to the corps,

37:53.320 --> 37:54.924
and he served his country well.

37:55.040 --> 37:56.883
Yes, he did.

37:57.000 --> 37:59.241
So did we all.

37:59.320 --> 38:00.765
Every one of us here.

38:00.880 --> 38:03.724
And we'd do it again
if we had the chance.

38:03.840 --> 38:06.127
What's going on, Sal?

38:06.240 --> 38:08.527
I don't know.
That's-that's why I'm asking.

38:08.600 --> 38:11.251
Shouldn't we be making
funeral arrangements?

38:11.280 --> 38:13.044
Isn't that why we're here?

38:13.120 --> 38:14.565
One second.

38:14.640 --> 38:17.041
Now, were you there
when this happened?

38:17.120 --> 38:18.645
No, I wasn't.

38:20.240 --> 38:21.480
So, where were you?

38:21.560 --> 38:24.131
With all due respect, sir,

38:24.200 --> 38:26.282
that is none of your business.

38:26.360 --> 38:28.408
Oh.

38:28.480 --> 38:29.891
Oh, I see.

38:29.960 --> 38:32.247
With all due respect...

38:33.840 --> 38:37.811
Doc ought to be able to talk
to somebody who was there.

38:37.960 --> 38:40.042
You weren't.

38:41.080 --> 38:42.127
All right.

38:42.200 --> 38:44.043
Were you?

38:53.840 --> 38:56.002
Yes, sir, I was there.

38:57.720 --> 38:59.165
Very well.

38:59.280 --> 39:02.170
Lance Corporal Washington,
tell them what happened.

39:30.040 --> 39:35.001
So, where we at
with all of this?

39:35.080 --> 39:38.323
Pretty much
where we were before.

39:38.400 --> 39:40.971
Doc wants his son's face back.

39:42.000 --> 39:44.401
Can't blame him for that.

39:47.440 --> 39:49.727
Called my wife.

39:49.800 --> 39:52.371
I'm going home.

39:52.440 --> 39:54.681
I'll be taking the bus.

39:54.760 --> 39:57.206
So you're quittin'?

39:57.280 --> 39:59.282
Quittin' what?

40:01.520 --> 40:03.443
Why don't we find out?

40:11.280 --> 40:15.001
So, Doc, what, uh,

40:15.080 --> 40:17.447
what are we gonna do here?

40:18.880 --> 40:21.406
I can't bury him at Arlington.
Not now.

40:22.880 --> 40:25.611
He qualifies and he deserves that honor.
Here.

40:25.680 --> 40:27.523
This is what he looked like.

40:27.600 --> 40:29.204
Can I see it?

40:29.320 --> 40:31.926
Handsome boy.
Wow. Yeah.

40:32.040 --> 40:34.566
High school girls
were crazy about him.

40:35.880 --> 40:38.451
My handsome boy.

40:38.560 --> 40:40.608
I'm taking Larry home.

40:40.720 --> 40:43.371
Sir, I can assure you
that is a bad decision

40:43.440 --> 40:46.887
and you will come to regret it.

40:46.960 --> 40:48.530
Sir, sir, sir, sir.

40:48.600 --> 40:50.523
Please stop.
- Sir, sir.

40:50.600 --> 40:53.444
The marines will transport
the body for you,

40:53.560 --> 40:56.769
at no cost to you,
anywhere you choose.

40:56.840 --> 40:58.205
Sir, sir...

40:58.280 --> 41:00.408
Sir, stop.

41:02.360 --> 41:04.806
I cannot legally release
the lance corporal's body

41:04.880 --> 41:06.928
to anyone,
except a licensed mortician.

41:08.280 --> 41:10.123
Or a clergyman.

41:11.120 --> 41:12.360
Isn't that so, Colonel?

41:13.800 --> 41:14.801
Correct.

41:14.920 --> 41:17.321
Well...

41:18.480 --> 41:19.561
it looks like...

41:21.160 --> 41:24.323
...that will be me.

41:27.280 --> 41:28.884
Lads.

41:45.680 --> 41:48.286
Here we go.

41:48.400 --> 41:51.210
Yeah. There.

41:57.120 --> 41:58.531
Not gonna fit.

42:00.240 --> 42:02.004
How you gonna get him home now?

42:02.120 --> 42:05.283
What you gonna do,
Sal, strap the coffin to the roof of your car?

42:07.200 --> 42:08.645
We could do that.

42:08.720 --> 42:11.530
Just need a little help
lifting it up, huh?

42:11.600 --> 42:13.807
Maybe we can get that kid
with the fucked-up ear.

42:13.880 --> 42:14.961
Don't be ridiculous.

42:15.040 --> 42:16.201
Why not?

42:16.320 --> 42:17.810
You know a better way to be?

42:17.880 --> 42:20.963
You wish you could be ridiculous,
but it's too late now.

42:21.040 --> 42:24.283
Doc, you've got to let the
government transport the body.

42:24.360 --> 42:26.169
I mean, it's the kind of thing
they're good at.

42:26.240 --> 42:28.208
L-I don't like
the government right now.

42:28.320 --> 42:29.810
Well, you don't have to.

42:29.880 --> 42:31.291
I don't trust it anymore.

42:31.400 --> 42:34.165
Hey, you know what,
we could rent a truck.

42:34.280 --> 42:36.965
You know what, let's do that.
Uh, you take the car.

42:37.040 --> 42:39.008
We'll stay here.

42:39.080 --> 42:40.525
Go find a truck.
- All right.

42:40.560 --> 42:43.325
And pay for it out of that.
One truck, comin' up.

42:43.400 --> 42:46.802
I'm coming with you, Sal.
You can drop me at the bus station.

42:46.880 --> 42:49.690
I think I got to be getting
back home now, Doc.

42:51.080 --> 42:54.004
I understand, Mueller.
I'm sorry I dragged you all the way up here.

42:54.080 --> 42:56.321
I really thought I could be
of some help to you, you know.

42:56.400 --> 42:58.482
I mean, I thought
we were going to a funeral.

42:58.560 --> 43:02.326
We are going to a funeral. Just looks like
it's gonna take a little longer to get there.

43:02.400 --> 43:04.004
It's okay.

43:04.080 --> 43:07.163
I'm just glad I got a chance
to... see you again.

43:10.440 --> 43:12.841
I'm very happy
I got to see you again, Doc.

43:16.920 --> 43:19.161
God bless you, Doc.

43:19.280 --> 43:21.203
Keep you in my prayers.

43:22.960 --> 43:25.691
And bless you, too, lad.

43:35.640 --> 43:37.369
Let me ask you something,

43:37.440 --> 43:39.602
man-to-man, hmm?

43:41.720 --> 43:43.882
You ever wonder...

43:43.960 --> 43:47.601
what would've happened,
way back then, if we hadn't...

43:48.440 --> 43:52.445
Doc wouldn't have ended up doing two
years in the brig, that's for sure.

43:53.480 --> 43:58.168
And you and me,
we... wouldn't had to seen what we did.

43:58.280 --> 43:59.486
And what was that?

44:00.800 --> 44:02.484
Are you shittin' me?

44:03.400 --> 44:04.925
You tellin' me you don't remember?

44:05.000 --> 44:07.002
I remember a lot of shit.

44:09.240 --> 44:11.288
What are you talking about?

44:11.360 --> 44:13.601
A certain platoon buddy
getting shot,

44:15.000 --> 44:16.968
writhing around
on the ground dying,

44:17.040 --> 44:19.281
with nothing to give him
to ease his pain

44:19.360 --> 44:21.488
'cause we had already taken
all the morphine.

44:21.600 --> 44:24.490
God rest his soul.

44:24.640 --> 44:26.927
There wasn't nothin'
we could do at that point.

44:27.000 --> 44:29.526
And we did nothin'.

44:31.800 --> 44:34.167
And sometimes
you got to do a little more.

44:49.320 --> 44:51.482
I have a van
that would work for you.

44:51.560 --> 44:53.961
All right.
But I think you might be happier

44:54.040 --> 44:56.327
with a truck that's got
a hydraulic tail lift.

44:56.400 --> 44:57.845
Oh.

44:57.920 --> 44:59.843
Hydraulic lift.
I like that, huh?

44:59.920 --> 45:01.809
What will you be hauling?

45:01.880 --> 45:05.282
Oh, you know, a truck
with a lift will handle it.

45:05.360 --> 45:08.330
Will you be dropping it off back here
or at another location?

45:08.400 --> 45:09.970
Uh...

45:10.040 --> 45:12.122
Don't you know?

45:12.200 --> 45:14.806
No, I guess
I'll be dropping it off here.

45:14.880 --> 45:16.166
And when will that be?

45:17.160 --> 45:18.650
What you lookin' at me for?

45:18.720 --> 45:21.963
I don't know.
How many days would it...?

45:22.040 --> 45:24.122
You don't know how long
you're going to need it?

45:24.240 --> 45:26.891
No, I don't know how long I'll need it.
Give me a week.

45:27.000 --> 45:28.490
Oh, yeah.

45:28.560 --> 45:30.005
A week, he says.

45:30.120 --> 45:33.681
Mueller, come on.
It's out of your hands, all right?

45:33.720 --> 45:35.802
Why don't you sit down,
take a load off,

45:35.880 --> 45:38.360
and let the mountain come
to Muhammad, all right?

45:39.720 --> 45:41.085
Chill.
All right?

45:43.320 --> 45:45.482
I need to see your driver's license.
- Yeah.

45:47.320 --> 45:49.243
Here you go.

45:50.720 --> 45:51.767
Ooh.

45:52.880 --> 45:54.530
These are free, right?

45:54.600 --> 45:56.011
Norfolk, Virginia?

45:56.080 --> 45:57.320
Yeah.

45:57.440 --> 45:58.680
Got to live somewhere.

45:59.800 --> 46:01.086
Will you be the only driver?

46:01.200 --> 46:03.362
Uh, no, no, I'll have some help.

46:03.440 --> 46:06.046
Then I'll need to see
the other driver's license.

46:06.120 --> 46:08.726
- Is it this gentleman here?
- ... thy rod

46:08.800 --> 46:12.247
and thy staff, they comfort me.
- His holiness?

46:12.320 --> 46:16.689
No, no.
His holiness can hardly walk,

46:16.760 --> 46:19.923
let alone handle a big rig
with a hydraulic lift.

46:20.000 --> 46:21.570
Whoever...
I'll need their license.

46:21.640 --> 46:23.244
...I will dwell
in the house of the Lord.

46:23.320 --> 46:25.448
What are you doing, with the bouncing?
What is that?

46:25.560 --> 46:27.164
I'm speaking a psalm.

46:27.240 --> 46:28.526
A psalm?
- Mm.

46:28.600 --> 46:30.204
Oh.

46:30.280 --> 46:34.763
As in, a psalm-a bin Laden.

46:34.840 --> 46:37.241
So, you are the only driver?

46:37.320 --> 46:39.243
Yes, ma'am, I be the wheelman.

46:40.480 --> 46:41.811
How will you be paying?

46:41.920 --> 46:45.322
Oh. Okay.

46:45.400 --> 46:47.323
Take it out of this.

46:47.400 --> 46:48.481
♪ That's the jingle bell ♪

46:48.600 --> 46:51.206
♪ That's the jingle bell rock ♪

46:54.280 --> 46:56.169
16 to 60,

46:56.280 --> 46:59.204
you put a dude behind the wheel
of a big rig like this,

46:59.280 --> 47:00.486
you're gonna feel like hot shit.

47:00.600 --> 47:04.002
This is a rented U-Haul
with an automatic transmission.

47:04.080 --> 47:06.242
This is bigger than anything
you ever handled.

47:06.320 --> 47:08.084
Sal, Doc's boy is dead.

47:08.160 --> 47:09.571
Try not to forget that.

47:09.680 --> 47:12.411
I haven't forgotten that.

47:12.480 --> 47:14.403
Jesus.

47:14.480 --> 47:16.801
But we're still alive, right?
Praise God.

47:16.880 --> 47:19.247
With time ticking fast away.

47:19.320 --> 47:22.608
So if there's one minute that's not too
terrible, I'd like to try to enjoy it.

47:22.680 --> 47:23.920
All right.

47:24.000 --> 47:26.082
I mean, you used to be
up for some fun.

47:26.160 --> 47:27.650
I still am.
- Oh, yeah.

47:27.720 --> 47:29.404
As long as it's right
in God's eyes.

47:29.480 --> 47:31.482
What is that, "God's eyes"?

47:31.560 --> 47:32.721
Wha-What...
God don't have any eyes.

47:32.840 --> 47:34.604
Oh, yes, He does.

47:34.680 --> 47:36.808
Oh, yeah.
God has eyes and He has ears.

47:36.880 --> 47:38.370
Yeah.
And He hears every insult

47:38.480 --> 47:40.050
- that you send His way.
- Geez.

47:40.160 --> 47:43.243
You believe me when I tell you, Sergeant,
there will be a reckoning.

47:43.320 --> 47:44.685
Oh, a reckoning.

47:44.840 --> 47:46.365
Yeah, God as my witness.
All right.

47:46.480 --> 47:47.811
I can assure you of that.

47:47.880 --> 47:49.848
Well, great, then,
because I reckon

47:49.880 --> 47:51.723
that I would take
that opportunity

47:51.840 --> 47:54.002
to stand at attention
and say to God,

47:54.080 --> 47:57.050
"Hey! Where were You when the...

47:57.160 --> 48:00.289
"raping children and the-the
genocide and all that?

48:00.360 --> 48:02.681
"Where were You
when they flew airplanes

48:02.760 --> 48:06.526
"into the buildings and killed thousands of people
"who were just going to work?

48:06.600 --> 48:08.841
"Where were You when Doc's kid

48:08.880 --> 48:11.486
"was just buying Cokes
for his buddies

48:11.560 --> 48:14.370
"and some raghead come up
and shoot his face off?

48:14.440 --> 48:15.851
Huh?
Where were You?"

48:15.920 --> 48:18.651
Yeah, you see,
I'm not gonna stand there

48:18.720 --> 48:20.688
and try to explain myself
to Him,

48:20.760 --> 48:22.728
I'm gonna make God
explain Himself to me.

48:22.840 --> 48:25.525
Oh, all right.
Yeah, and I think by the end of it, He'll say,

48:25.600 --> 48:30.208
"Hey, come on. Get in here.

48:30.280 --> 48:32.886
"You?
You're my kind of dude.

48:32.960 --> 48:35.088
You, give me one of these."

48:36.640 --> 48:38.165
All right, well,
good luck with that.

48:38.240 --> 48:39.844
I'll be praying for you,
you hear?

48:39.920 --> 48:43.208
Yeah, well, I'll be hoping
for the same thing.

48:43.280 --> 48:45.760
But, boy,
if it's a tight-ass God,

48:45.880 --> 48:47.928
then I am fucked.
- Yeah.

48:48.040 --> 48:51.010
And I think it's time for that lube
job on that plate in your head.

48:51.080 --> 48:53.367
Hey, stay the fuck away
from my plate, all right?

48:53.440 --> 48:55.283
I'm picking up WOR from New York.

48:55.400 --> 48:57.004
I'm homesick.

48:57.120 --> 48:59.566
Yeah.
- Hey, wait a minute. Maybe...

49:01.120 --> 49:02.884
Oh, no, no, no.
Well...

49:02.960 --> 49:06.043
You have to turn that shit off.
- So, you know about this stuff, right?

49:06.120 --> 49:07.610
Oh, man.
- All right.

49:07.720 --> 49:11.327
So, you know, I have been known
to get in a face or two.

49:11.400 --> 49:13.721
But even I'm offended
by this stuff.

49:13.800 --> 49:15.404
I mean,
it's damn hard to dance to.

49:15.480 --> 49:19.201
Well, that is one thing that we can finally agree on.
- There you go.

49:19.280 --> 49:23.205
Aren't you a little ashamed
being an African-American?

49:23.280 --> 49:25.726
Mm, no, not really.
Why should I be?

49:25.800 --> 49:29.202
Because being a dignified
gentleman such as yourself,

49:29.280 --> 49:31.328
you would be the first to agree

49:31.440 --> 49:35.729
that this is so far away
from, like, Motown, man.

49:35.800 --> 49:37.802
Right? Well, I have
nothing to be ashamed of.

49:37.920 --> 49:39.649
I mean, this dude is white.

49:39.760 --> 49:42.764
♪ Ever since Prince turned
Himself into a symbol ♪

49:44.480 --> 49:46.562
"White."
- That's affirmative.

49:46.640 --> 49:47.641
Yeah. Yeah.
- White is right.

49:47.760 --> 49:48.966
This guy's white.

49:49.000 --> 49:51.731
Word to God.
- This is coming out of a white mouth?

49:51.840 --> 49:53.490
A white sewer mouth.

49:53.600 --> 49:55.329
Bullshit.
- Mm, nope.

49:55.440 --> 49:56.965
I bullshit you not.

49:57.000 --> 49:58.570
Mm-hmm.
- Fuck me.

49:58.680 --> 50:00.091
♪ Hey ♪

50:00.160 --> 50:02.401
Well, then, I ought to be
a little ashamed.

50:02.480 --> 50:05.802
Only I never really identified
with the white race.

50:05.880 --> 50:08.008
Oh, really?

50:08.120 --> 50:10.964
No. Nothing.
Oh, now I'm curious.

50:11.000 --> 50:14.447
Nope.
Now, what race do you, uh, identify with?

50:14.520 --> 50:16.727
Green.

50:16.800 --> 50:19.770
Green?
- Yeah. The corps.

50:19.840 --> 50:22.320
Okay.
I mean,

50:22.400 --> 50:24.641
it's really the only culture
I ever...

50:24.720 --> 50:26.643
really thought made sense.

50:26.720 --> 50:28.449
♪ Nah-nah, nah-nah-nah ♪

50:28.520 --> 50:30.284
All right.

50:30.360 --> 50:31.885
Let me ask you something.

50:32.000 --> 50:33.047
Hmm?

50:33.160 --> 50:34.366
♪ Nah, nah-nah, nah-nah ♪

50:34.480 --> 50:36.130
Do you ever miss it?

50:36.200 --> 50:38.726
Not for one blessed minute.

50:39.880 --> 50:41.803
I don't believe you.
That's all right.

50:41.880 --> 50:43.211
You don't believe in God either,

