01:06:03.960 --> 01:06:05.928
Except you.

01:06:05.960 --> 01:06:08.042
Please.

01:06:14.640 --> 01:06:16.927
I think I'll go back
and talk to him.

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:18.968
Oh, I'm sure he'll enjoy that.

01:06:19.040 --> 01:06:21.611
Tell him he should come
up here and sit with us.

01:06:21.680 --> 01:06:22.761
All right.

01:06:22.840 --> 01:06:25.127
I'll extend an invitation.

01:06:37.480 --> 01:06:39.847
There we go.

01:06:41.480 --> 01:06:43.562
This is bleak, man.

01:06:45.320 --> 01:06:47.482
You're welcome.
- What for?

01:06:47.560 --> 01:06:52.168
What for?
Are you on a train in Baghdad?

01:06:52.240 --> 01:06:54.686
No, you are not.
- I guess not.

01:06:56.840 --> 01:06:58.649
Yeah, TDY.

01:06:58.720 --> 01:07:00.643
Sometimes it's fun.

01:07:00.720 --> 01:07:03.644
Sometimes it's a bitch.
No, I don't mind.

01:07:03.720 --> 01:07:06.007
He was my best friend.

01:07:06.040 --> 01:07:10.045
Yeah, you didn't, uh, what,
hang with the brothers?

01:07:10.120 --> 01:07:11.770
What the fuck is that?

01:07:11.880 --> 01:07:14.611
I don't know.
I saw it on the MTV, I think.

01:07:14.680 --> 01:07:16.125
It's not a rule.

01:07:16.200 --> 01:07:18.009
No, I'm not saying it's a rule.

01:07:18.040 --> 01:07:19.804
I liked the dude.

01:07:19.880 --> 01:07:22.281
He had my back and I had his.

01:07:22.360 --> 01:07:24.966
He was honest,
said what he thought.

01:07:25.040 --> 01:07:26.963
Oh, yeah.
Simple, in a good way.

01:07:27.040 --> 01:07:28.326
Never had an attitude.

01:07:28.400 --> 01:07:30.368
Sounds a lot like his father.

01:07:30.520 --> 01:07:32.124
Even the honest part?

01:07:33.200 --> 01:07:34.486
Doc?

01:07:34.560 --> 01:07:36.085
Doc is not a dishonest man.

01:07:36.160 --> 01:07:37.491
What about the brig time?

01:07:37.560 --> 01:07:39.562
Fuck, that could've happened
to any one of us.

01:07:39.680 --> 01:07:41.284
